    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong>&nbsp;<em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 142</em>,&nbsp;<em>PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 469</em></p>\n<p><strong>Aura</strong>&nbsp;moderate conjuration&nbsp;<strong>CL</strong>&nbsp;9th</p>\n<p><strong>Slot</strong>&nbsp;weapon quality;&nbsp;<strong>Price</strong>&nbsp;+1 bonus;&nbsp;<strong>Weight</strong>&nbsp;-</p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\"><img style=\"margin: 3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"PFS Legal\" src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" /><strong>Description</strong></h3>\n<p>A&nbsp;<em>ghost touch&nbsp;</em>weapon deals damage normally against incorporeal creatures, regardless of its bonus. An incorporeal creature's 50% reduction in damage from corporeal sources does not apply to attacks made against it with&nbsp;<em>ghost touch&nbsp;</em>weapons. The weapon can be picked up and moved by an incorporeal creature at any time. A manifesting ghost can wield the weapon against corporeal foes. Essentially, a&nbsp;<em>ghost touch&nbsp;</em>weapon counts as both corporeal or incorporeal. This special ability can only be placed on melee weapons and ammunition.</p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Construction</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>&nbsp;Craft Magic Arms and Armor,&nbsp;<em>plane shift</em>;&nbsp;<strong>Price</strong>&nbsp;-</p>",
